 Veteran Broadcaster Larry King Veteran broadcaster Larry King, has tested positive for coronavirus and is being treated at a hospital in Los Angeles, according to CNN. Sources close to his family told his former employer CNN that he has been at Cedars-Sinai Medical Centre for over a week. Larry King, 87, is said to have faced several health problems in recent years, including heart attacks. King, whose career spans over 60 years, has won multiple accolades, including two Peabody Awards and an Emmy.